It is the regional capital and was officially founded in July 1966. The city was used as a base of operations by the South African Defence Force (SADF) during the South African Border War. Oshakati is divided into the electoral constituencies of Oshakati East and Oshakati West. ==References== Category:Oshana Region Category:Towns in Africa Category:Settlements in Namibia
